    <b>Microsoft copy-protection could force users to lie.</b><br>
    <font size=1><b>Date:</b> Tuesday, January 23 @ 06:43:37 CST<br><b>Topic:</b> Microsoft<br><br>
    </center><font size=2>
    ZDNet points out a workaround to Microsoft's latest copy protection scheme. Under the new system, Microsoft requires Microsoft Office users to register each copy they install before that copy will work. Under their license agreement, only two copies can be installed. By lying, according to the article, you can get a third copy installed.<br>
